UX and product design‚Ä¶ what‚Äôs the difference? ü§îYou might have heard these roles being used interchangeably, and they are quite similar‚Äîbut each have different overall focus in their job! Swipe and read to learn more üëÄ***On one hand, UX design is‚Ä¶üëâ focused on creating beautiful interfaces and building seamless interaction, and ensure the whole user experience is enjoyable‚≠êÔ∏è is a more specialized role as they have a more specific, design-oriented focus in their responsibilitiesüß∞ experience can be involved with interaction design, visual design, UX research, and other similar rolesOn the other hand, product design‚Ä¶üîé is involved with the entire product creation process, with a more business-oriented focus as they are responsible for discovering and defining a problem and creating a design solution‚ú® sometimes associated with physical design, also known as industrial designüí≠ experience can be involved in project and/or product management, UX design, and more!***#uwaterloo #ux #uxdesign #productdesign #designtips

So grateful to have been part of the incredible Figma prototyping workshop organized by @uw_ux featuring @instamiggi and @mdeandesign !!Miggi is an absolute legend. Truly one of the most engaging presenters I‚Äôve ever seen.I‚Äôve been a huge fan of his ever since attending his keynote speech at the designathon hosted by @ux.laurier back in March. He talked about his passion for drawing on coffee cups and sharing his work on social media, emphasizing the importance of establishing an authentic online presence. He was a huge inspiration for me in my decision to start my design account and share my journey with the world.On top of that, Miggi‚Äôs and Mallory‚Äôs dedication to helping junior designers improve through education and mentorship is truly admirable, and I look up to them immensely. I‚Äôll continue to work hard with the goal of one day being able to give back to the design community in the same way.I should have added a clip of me watching the workshop demos with my mouth open üòÆ It was truly eye-opening to see just how powerful Figma‚Äôs prototyping features are.What really stood out to me during the workshop was the power of interactive components. You can prototype a component to have a certain interaction, then create many instances of that component within a frame, essentially making the interaction modular. This significantly reduces the number of frames and connections needed to prototype interactions such as the multiple states of input fields (toggles, buttons, etc.).I gained so many valuable insights from this workshop, and I wanted to say a huge thank you to everyone involved in making this happen! ü´∂üèºP.S. the merch was absolutely insane!!
